-ahead-19833871.htm","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-27T14:12:41","source":"CNBC TV18"},{"id":"260127140556036","title":"JSW Energy and Godrej Consumer Products shares plunged 10% post-Q3 results, while India Cements rose 5%.\nJSW Energy's profit grew 150% YoY, but missed estimates; Godrej Consumer's net profit declined; India Cements showed operational improvements.","summary":"JSW Energy and Godrej Consumer Products shares plunged 10% post-Q3 results, while India Cements rose 5%.\nJSW Energy's profit grew 150% YoY, but missed estimates; Godrej Consumer's net profit declined; India Cements showed operational improvements.","url":"https://www.moneycontrol.com/europe/?url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/business/markets/q3-results-impact-jsw-energy-godrej-consumer-products-shares-plunge-10-india-cements-up-5-13791944.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-27T12:47:36","source":"Moneycontrol"},{"id":"260124138943623","title":"Godrej Consumer's Q3 profit dipped to INR 4.98B due to Indonesia weakness, labour codes.\nNet profit marginally fell from INR 4.98B YoY, impacted by one-time charges.","summary":"Godrej Consumer's Q3 profit dipped to INR 4.98B due to Indonesia weakness, labour codes.\nNet profit marginally fell from INR 4.98B YoY, impacted by one-time charges.","url":"https://brandequity.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/business-of-brands/indias-godrej-consumer-profit-edges-lower-on-indonesia-weakness-one-off-charge/127389630","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-24T16:46:54","source":"The Economic Times"},{"id":"802755152001372928","title":"Morgan Stanley retains Overweight rating on Godrej Consumer with a target of 1,291.\nThe rating is based on consistent growth and stable margins.","summary":"Morgan Stanley retains Overweight rating on Godrej Consumer with a target of 1,291.\nThe rating is based on consistent growth and stable margins.","url":"https://sqst.in/shareMessage?msgId=802755152001372903","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-24T09:52:22","source"